verbose_text: Receptor activator for nuclear factor-kappaB ligand (RANKL) is vital for the formation and function of osteoclasts, and binding of RANKL to its receptor RANK results in activation of the nuclear factor (NF)-kappaB, mitogen activated protein kinase (MAPK) and protein kinase B (AKT) signaling pathways.
